Element ui:panel
Namespace https://github.com/bordertech/wcomponents/namespace/ui/v1.0
Annotations
WPanel provides a generic content container and a number of special purpose container and layout components. It is a fundamental UI layout tool.

Attributes
QName Type Default Use Annotation
accessKey restriction of xs:string optional
Sets a single modified key access key for a control. This attribute should be used with caution as:
  • some user agents reserve some keys for internal use and do not expose them to the client for use as access keys; and
  • some keys may clash or cause issues with use of various assistive technologies.
buttonId xs:NMTOKEN optional
Provides the id of a WButton which can be used as a default submit button for all data-input components in the panel which support form submission on ENTER key press. May be overridden by individual controls which implement a similar attribute.
class xs:string optional
Provides the ability to pass an HTML class attribute onto the root output element.
hidden xs:boolean false optional
The component will be in a hidden state if "true".
id xs:ID required
The unique identifier for the component.
mode restriction of xs:NMTOKEN optional
Indicates the content display mode for the component.
title xs:string optional
A human readable title for the panel. Required for @type "action" and "chrome" but optional otherwise.
track xs:boolean false optional
Indicates that the component should take part in web analytics tracking.
type restriction of xs:NMTOKEN optional
Indicates the semantic meaning and/or stylistic options to be applied to the panel. Some types provide for explicit block level semantics and style and others are merely stylistic.

Element ui:panel / ui:gridlayout
Namespace https://github.com/bordertech/wcomponents/namespace/ui/v1.0
Annotations
Provides a layout mechanism for WPanel which attempts to apply a regular grid to the components in the panel.

Instance

  <ui:cell>{0,unbounded}</ui:cell>
</ui:gridlayout>
Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
cols xs:unsignedInt required
Indicates the number of columns to render in the grid. A value of zero indicates fixed rows, variable columns depending on content.
hgap xs:positiveInteger optional
The horizontal space between content components in the layout in pixels. This may be adjusted by the theme and/or user agent.
rows xs:unsignedInt required
Indicates the number of rows to render in the grid. A value of zero indicates fixed columns, variable rows depending on content.
vgap xs:positiveInteger optional
The vertical space between content components in the layout in pixels. This may be adjusted by the theme and/or user agent.

QName Type Use Annotation
align restriction of xs:NMTOKEN required
Indicates the flow arrangement

            </xs:annotation>

        </xs:restriction>
      </xs:simpleType>
    </xs:attribute>

Element ui:panel / ui:columnlayout
Namespace https://github.com/bordertech/wcomponents/namespace/ui/v1.0
Annotations
Provides a layout mechanism for WPanel which attempts to apply a consistent row and column set to the components in the panel. This differs from a grid layout in that the columns are not constrained to a uniform width or horizontal alignment of content.

Attribute ui:panel / ui:flowlayout / @valign
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
Indicates the vertical alignment of components within a horizontal flow. If not set then the flow default is determined by the theme. These differences can be both subtle and arcane and only baseline will give totally consistent results in all modern browsers.
Type restriction of xs:NMTOKEN
Properties
content simple
Facets
enumeration top
The components should attempt to arrange themselves so that they align at the top of the content box of the parent container.
enumeration middle
The components should attempt to arrange themselves so that they align at the middle of the content boxes each content cell.
enumeration baseline
The components should attempt to arrange themselves so that they align at the baseline for text of each content cell.
enumeration bottom
The components should attempt to arrange themselves so that they align at the bottom of the content box of the parent container.
Used by
Element ui:panel/ui:flowlayout
